    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid over a high heat</p> <p>Once hot, add a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and the <strong>pancetta lardons\u00a0</strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until crispy</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-pancetta-and-baby-kale-minestrone/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle\u00a0</p> <p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>brown</strong>\u00a0<strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[</span></strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>s]</strong></span></p> <p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-pancetta-and-baby-kale-minestrone/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>pancetta</strong> is crispy, add the <strong>diced\u00a0</strong><strong>onion\u00a0</strong>to the pan with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook over a medium heat for 3-4 min or until soft\u00a0</p> <p>Once soft, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>dried\u00a0oregano</strong> to the pan and cook for a further 1 min</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-pancetta-and-baby-kale-minestrone/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>chicken stock cube</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span> in 650ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.1L] </span><strong>boiled water</strong>\u00a0\u2013 this is your <strong>chicken stock\u00a0</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-pancetta-and-baby-kale-minestrone/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chicken\u00a0stock</strong>, <strong>conchiglie</strong>,<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong> and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[3 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> to the pan</p> <p>Cover with a lid and cook over a medium heat for 12-14 min or until the <strong>conchiglie</strong> is\u00a0cooked</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-pancetta-and-baby-kale-minestrone/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, pick the<strong> basil leaves</strong> from their stems and discard the stems</p> <p>Chop a couple of <strong>basil leaves</strong> finely, leaving the rest whole</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-pancetta-and-baby-kale-minestrone/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse the <strong>cannellini beans\u00a0</strong></p> <p>Once the conchiglie is cooked, add the drained<strong> cannellini</strong>\u00a0<strong>beans</strong>,<strong>\u00a0whole basil leaves</strong>\u00a0(save the chopped basil for garnish) and <strong>baby kale</strong>\u00a0to the pan</p> <p>Cook for 1-2 min or\u00a0until the baby kale has wilted and the cannellini beans are warmed through</p> <p>Season generously with both <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>\u00a0\u2013 this is your <strong>pancetta\u00a0minestrone</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-pancetta-and-baby-kale-minestrone/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> pancetta minestrone</strong>\u00a0in bowls, and garnish with the<strong>\u00a0chopped basil\u00a0</strong></p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
